The paper discusses algorithmic strategies for playing two-player games, which involves artificial intelligence (AI) techniques. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with game theory (GT) and computational complexity (CC) as it discusses the objective of winning the game and minimizing the number of questions asked. The paper also introduces new types of games, which could fall under the category of data structures (DS) and machine learning (LG).
